Chas Owens asked:

> Would this work as well?
>
> say :to(END);
> \x{3D}begin POD
> blah blah blah
> \x{3D}end POD
> END


Yes, except for the :to actually needing to be qq:to (which was wrong
all the way through these examples, BTW).

You could also just use:

say qq:to(END);
\=begin POD
blah blah blah
\=end POD
END


